</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB2456:v98#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB2456"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              2456-&#xA;                AMENDED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Amended
               IN </span><span style=" text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 1em">
                Assembly
              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">March 16, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2456</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Harabedian<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act<font color="#B30000"><strike> relating to vehicles.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> to add Section 68705 to the Government Code, relating to courts.</i></font></span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2456, as amended, Harabedian.
                          <font color="#B30000"><strike>Vehicles: vehicle accidents. </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Courts: Commission on Judicial Performance.</i></font></span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">The California Constitution establishes the Commission on Judicial Performance and authorizes the commission to disqualify, suspend, retire, or censure a judge for specified acts of misconduct or for disability that seriously interferes with the performance of the judge’s duties or that is, or is likely to become, permanent. The California Constitution requires the commission to make rules for the investigation of judges and authorizes the commission to provide for the confidentiality of complaints to, and investigations by, the commission. Existing statutory law also governs procedures for the conduct of these investigations. Existing law requires state and local departments and their employees to cooperate with the commission in an investigation conducted by the commission.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would authorize courts to display on their public internet website information that the Commission on Judicial Performance prepares and provides that clearly and concisely presents the Commission on Judicial Performance’s mission, its process for submitting a complaint, and information about what constitutes a violation of the Code of Judicial Ethics.</div></i></font><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>Existing law imposes specified requirements, including requirements related to accident reports, on the driver of a vehicle involved in an an accident resulting in injury or death, as provided.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would state the intent of the Legislature to enact subsequent legislation related to vehicle accidents.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase"><font color="#B30000"><strike>NO</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>YES</i></font></span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.21914391805575606"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 68705 is added to the Government Code, to read:</i></font></div><div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div id="id_8DCDF950-85C4-4AF1-A0DB-F3D3DEC777C7"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">68705.</h6> Courts may display on their public internet website information that the Commission on Judicial Performance prepares and provides that clearly and concisely presents the Commission on Judicial Performance’s mission, its processes for submitting a complaint, and information about what constitutes a violation of the Code of Judicial Ethics.</div></p></div></div></i></font></div></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:BillSection id="id_3238D609-93D2-4E54-98C7-D471DA8BA63F"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SECTION 1.</caml:Num><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>It is the intent of the Legislature to enact subsequent legislation related to vehicle accidents.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:BillSection></strike></font></div></div></body></html>
